<section id="workflow" class="sheet section">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="section-kicker">Workflow</p>
    <h2>Human editing, machine checks, quiet tooling</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="two-up">
    <div>
      <p>
        Validation is handled by a small Node script that parses Markdown frontmatter, classifies each `L10N` document by its path,
        and checks it against the matching schema.
      </p>
      <p>
        `mise.toml` carries the Node runtime and the common tasks, so anyone cloning the repository gets the same commands and a predictable local setup.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="terminal">
      <p class="terminal-title">Common commands</p>
      <pre><code>mise run install
mise run validate
mise run dev
mise run build</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
